The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: Home minister P. Chidambaram today met oil secretary R.S. Pandey to apprise himself of the discontentment among oil PSU executives with the recent hike in wages approved by the government. This was Chidambarams first meeting as the head of a four-member group set up by the Prime Minister to look into the demands of the oil PSU officers, who have announced an indefinite strike from January 7. In a bid to avert the strike, Chidambaram is believed to have assured of making recommendations within a months time, sources said.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The Centre wants to restrict the burden of fertiliser subsidy for 2009-10 fiscal at Rs 50,000, compared with Rs 1,02,000 crore earlier projected, as prices have plunged in the global markets.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: NTPC is facing severe coal shortages and heavily dependent on imports. The company hopes that the situation will start improving in three to four months.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 4: Sales in the manufacturing sector are likely to witness a slowdown for the quarter ended December because of a steep fall in commodity prices, the Centre for Monitoring Indian Economy said in a report.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The government has received nine fresh proposals for setting up special economic zones. The Board of Approval will consider the new proposals on January 15.                                                                                                                           
